# DevOps Standards

## Purpose
Keep deployments reproducible, observable, and safe to operate.

## Requirements
- externalize environment-specific configuration
- never hardcode secrets
- keep deployment steps reproducible and documented
- provide health checks and useful logging
- define rollback expectations for risky changes
- keep infrastructure changes understandable and reviewable
- prefer the simplest pipeline that satisfies reliability needs
- surface operational risks before rollout

## Apply When
- changing deployment pipelines
- modifying infrastructure configuration
- preparing production or staging rollouts
